Shah Jiwana is a town of Jhang District in the Punjab, Pakistan. it is located on the Jhang-Lalian road at 31°31'13N 72°20'21E 34 km from Jhang. Shah Jiwana or Shah Jeewna, is named after Syed Mahboob Alam, a famous Sufi saint of the Hussaini-Qalandari Order, of earlier times, whose famous shrine here is visited by many pilgrims each year. Template:29 Besakh (bikarmi) . The main lineal descendant and manager of the shrine at present is Makhdoom SyedFaisal Saleh Hayat.
The famous Shah Jewna Equine Stud Farm, owned by Syeda Abida Hussain, is also situated here.
